@page
@model HardwareInventoryTrackingSystem.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
@{
    Layout = null;
}
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <style>
        /* Page-wide styles */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .privacy-container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 1500px;
            background: #fff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px auto;
        }

            .privacy-container h1, .privacy-container h2 {
                color: #0056b3;
            }

            .privacy-container h1 {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }

            .privacy-container h2 {
                font-size: 1.5rem;
                margin-top: 20px;
            }

            .privacy-container p {
                margin: 10px 0;
            }

            .privacy-container ul {
                margin: 10px 0 10px 20px;
                padding: 0;
            }

                .privacy-container ul li {
                    margin-bottom: 8px;
                }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="privacy-container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 27, 2024</p>
        <p>Welcome to the Hardware Inventory System (the "System"). Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use the System to borrow hardware components from the laboratory. By using the System, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Full Name, Student ID, Email Address, Contact Information.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Borrowing history (items borrowed, date/time of transactions, return status), System access logs (e.g., IP address, timestamps).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To manage hardware borrowing transactions.</li>
            <li>To verify your identity as a student.</li>
            <li>To communicate with you regarding borrowing and returning hardware.</li>
            <li>To improve the System’s functionality and user experience.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your personal information will only be shared:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>With laboratory staff for transaction management and monitoring.</li>
            <li>With authorized university personnel to ensure compliance with policies.</li>
            <li>If required by law or to comply with legal obligations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy. Borrowing records may be kept for auditing or compliance purposes in line with university policies.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement security measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of sensitive data.</li>
            <li>Regular security assessments.</li>
            <li>Access controls limited to authorized personnel.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access and review your personal information.</li>
            <li>Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your information, subject to retention requirements for compliance.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at processor@addu.edu.ph.</p>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>The System may use cookies to enhance your experience. Cookies are small files stored on your device that help us track user activity and preferences. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though some features of the System may not function properly without them.</p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated through the System or via email. Your continued use of the System after updates constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> jrcfebiar@addu.edu.ph | nbhganzon@addu.edu.ph</li>
            <li><strong>Phone:</strong> +63 917 624 8695 | +63 966 461 4496</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>